    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "story_body",
      "label": "Story copy before quote",
      "default": "<p>Valor Communication started in Los Angeles in 1997 with a wholesale operation built for the people who actually move wireless accessories - independent dealers, regional distributors, master agents, and the buyers stocking shelves at retail. The work was practical from day one: get the right product built, priced, packed, shipped, and ready before demand turned into a missed sale.</p><p>That channel-first mindset shaped a company designed to last, scale, and keep pace with how wireless accessories actually sell. Tooling, packaging, freight, MOQs, terms, fulfillment, manufacturing, testing, and certifications were never background details - they were the operating system. <strong>Every part of the business was designed around what holds up at the point of sale</strong>, not what looks good in a corporate lookbook.</p><p>Nearly 30 years later, those wholesale roots have grown into a full-scale wireless accessory partner with the product depth, supply chain control, and channel reach to support demand across every major wireless path to sale.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "story_quote",
      "label": "Pull quote",
      "default": "We do not build brands and hope the channel catches up. We build brands made to move through it."
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "story_body_after_quote",
      "label": "Story copy after quote",
      "default": "<p>Today the operation spans <strong>250,000 square feet of fulfillment</strong> across California and Texas, a Shenzhen-based manufacturing arm running since 1999, and a portfolio of in-house brands covering protection, power, audio, attachables, and wearables. Product development, engineering, manufacturing, fulfillment, and custom programs now work as one connected system - from packaging through retail execution. Fewer handoffs, cleaner supply chains, more products ready where demand shows up.</p><p>Programs reach <strong>21,000+ retail locations at a 99% on-time delivery rate</strong> across major carrier networks, national retail, off-price chains, home improvement, OEM programs, and digital marketplaces. Retail intelligence, demand planning, inventory support, global logistics, and POS-ready integration help partners manage more than product availability - they help manage the systems that keep products stocked, moving, and selling.</p><p>What changed over those years is the depth of the operation. What didn't is the customer at the center of it: the operator selling phones at street level, the buyer stocking a planogram, the merchandiser picking next quarter's assortment, and the partner who needs the right products ready before the next ask hits.</p><p>The infrastructure scaled. The work didn't. <strong>Partners keep coming back because Valor keeps showing up.</strong></p>"
    },
